Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan. Bring to boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover; simmer until gizzard is tender, about 1 hour 30 minutes. Strain stock into medium bowl. Transfer neck, gizzard, and heart to bowl; cool. Trim meat from neck. Chop neck meat, gizzard, and heart. Transfer to small bowl; reserve for gravy. (Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover stock and giblets separately; chill.)
